spanGrp.span: so Ouma, say, Anna Kassie, do you know (?what) she said?
so Ouma, sê, Anna Kassie, ku ǁxaea ha ǂxoa,
Anna Kassie, weet jy wat sy gepraat het?
transcribed by ER in October 2007 and re-checked in October 2009; OK
I don't know , I don't know
ek weet nie, ek weet nie
meaning of second /ng/ unclear; might be two times the same /ng ǁu ǁxae/
maybe there is an /-a/ suffix at /ǁxae/; check
I haven't heard (that) she tells me
[ng ǁam] ǁam xa noxoba tyuu, ku ǀqxʼae na,
ek het nog nie gehoor (dat) sy vertel vir my nie
so that we hear what she says
nǀa tyuu, ng ku dyee ka,
lat ons hoor wat sy sê
dyee: meaning not really clear, 'do how' is just a guess
she is just a small ?, but she is wily
hy is mos so ʼn klein klimmeidjie, maar hy is mos politiek,
hy is mos so 'n klein ?klim?meidjie, maar hy is politiek
"klim-meidjie" oder so; so was wie ein kleines Mädchen, Enkelkind etc!!!
she knows things that I don't know
kua ǁxaea gunnke he ǁu ǁxaea,
sy ken goed wat ek nie ken nie
you see indeed she is small, she is (looks like) a small ghost
a ke mos nǀai, kua ǂʼain, ku ǀhoqo ʘuun,
jy sien mos sy is klein sy lyk soos 'n klein spookie
E first repeated /... ǂain, kua ku ǀhoqo ʘuun/; I think it is /ku ng ǀhoqo ʘuun/
